      <p id="Par31">We considered sample sizes of 300, 200 and 150 each with 1000 replicates. For each case, the average parameter estimates and their standard deviations were calculated. In addition, under the three different model selection criteria described above, the power of detecting a specific QTL segregation pattern for each QTL model was obtained by counting the number of runs out of the 1000 repeats in which the correct pattern was chosen.</p>
